<br>
The problem came when the mez caps came into place. You found that your mez/charm became impossible on most mobs. And you needed to carry around 2 sets of gear, normal and resist gear. It became time to refocus on the direction of your character’s stats. I started to focus on Mana and resists. Everyone makes there own choices at that point. Cause it's the gear at that point that drives you. <br>
<br>
I guess I am an enchanter who won’t give up my Charisma. I still keep it in the 220’s and buff the +50 Cha buff. Why? Cause I loved it when I charmed a named dragon in western wastes and freaked out my guild.   <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sheeanafuriae>SheeanaFuriae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(7/4/03 11:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int and Cha</span><hr size=1> My level 65 enchanter has 280 Int and with my cha buff, 280 cha.  I find a considerable difference in how often my mezzes, charms and even slows (although that might be my imagination) are resisted when I mindlessly forget to rebuff my cha while grouped.  <br>
<br>
If I had it to do again, with my Eurdite race, I would have put more points into Cha then Int as I've found it much easier to increase Int over time with items then cha.. and also I found pre-level 60 enchanters spells to be extremely mana effcient and inexpensive (with the exception of haste buffs and perhaps gok). Of couse now it doesn't really matter, Luclin and PoP have a lot more items that have both cha and int for casters and with aa abilities its certainly less of an issue to cap int/cha.  <br>
<br>
But, my point is, I find a considerable difference between having high points in cha and not having high points in cha.<br>
<br>
Oh and for you flamers out there, I am aware that the cap for int/cha is 255, but with aa, it does increase to cap at 280. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
